I remember finding a book in the Paineel library some time ago that described the history of Paineel and the Heretics etc. and it seemed to refer to the Heretics as followers of Bertoxxulous.<br>
Or was it all just my vile imagining?<br>
<br>
Luce <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderating inconsistently<br>since Jun 2002</span><br>  Posts: 1391<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/1/02 2:28:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2831.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bertoxxulous Heretics?</span><hr size=1> OOC: Paineel, Warrens, and Stonebrunt are all optional download zones.<br>
<br>
When EQ was released, the Heretics were on Bertoxxulous faction, and could only be necromancers.  They lived in a hut in Tox forest.<br>
<br>
A year or so after release, they added the Paineel zone, and added Shadowknights &amp; Clerics for heretics, and changed all of them to worship Cazic Thule.<br>
<br>
I'm not really sure why they changed the diety from Bertoxx to Cazic Thule.  I don't recall any lore explaining the change.<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eats Halflings</span><br>  Posts: 386<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/1/02 3:04:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2831.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/btk120/antoin.gif width=68 height=146></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm.</span><hr size=1> Only correlation I can think of is that Erudites have no disease resistance... <p>--Antoin Nolouj
